rs include detailed information on retail pricing as approved by the PUCT.\n\nFilename Tariff for Retail Delivery Service.pdf\n\nSize 3 MB\n\nFormat application/pdf\n\n### ONCOR RETAIL DELIVERY SERVICE RATE CODES\n\nThis downloadable file is a complete list of Oncor Retail Delivery Service Rate Codes. The codes are applicable to all retail electric providers (REP) receiving delivery service within Oncor's service area.\n\nFilename Rate Codes Info.pdf\n\nSize 75 KB\n\nFormat application/pdf\n\n### RESIDENTIAL DELIVERY SERVICE RATE COMPARISON\n\nCompare Oncor delivery service rates to other transmission and distribution service providers.\n\n### WHOLESALE TRANSMISSION SERVICE TARIFFS\n\nTransmission Service tariffs apply to wholesale transmission service within ERCOT and are approved by the PUCT. The tariffs comply with the Texas Utilities Code and PUCT Substantive Rule requirements that wholesale open access transmission service be provided on a nondiscriminatory basis to all wholesale transmission system users, including the company itself.\n\nFilename Transmission Tariff.pdf\n\nSize 1 MB\n\nFormat application/pdf\n\nFilename Oncor NTU Tariff for Transmission Service.pdf\n\nSize 1 MB\n\nFormat application/pdf\n\n### FERC TFO TARIFF\n\nThe Tariff for Transmission Service To, From and Over Certain HVDC Interconnections (FERC TFO Tariff) applies to wholesale transmission service, which utilizes the North or East HVDC interconnections between ERCOT and the Southwest Power Pool (SPP). This tariff is approved by the FERC.\n\nFilename FERC TFO TARIFF.pdf\n\nSize 319 KB\n\nFormat application/pdf\n\nReport power outage\n\nClick here for More Details.\n\nMyOncor Alerts\n\nDownload Our App\n\n### Follow Us\n\n### download our app\n\n#### What We Do\n\n##### Safety\n\n##### Economic Development\n\n##### External Affairs\n\n##### Regulatory\n\n##### Transmission System\n\n##### Electric Distribution System\n\n##### Advanced Metering Service\n\n#### PARTNERS\n\n##### REP Resource